      <div><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">Welcome to the seventh edition o=
f Noticing=2C rounding up the best new (and more than a few old) things of=
 the week. This is our second time around experimenting with a Sunday deli=
very date rather than Friday; please let us know what you think about it!<=
/p>

<h2 style=3D"color: #F00A0A;font-size: 22px;line-height: 27px;font-weight:=
 bold;margin: 35px 0 10px;">Twenty years later=2C still Jason from the blo=
ck</h2>
You should definitely check out <a href=3D"http://www.niemanlab.org/2018/0=
2/last-blog-standing-last-guy-dancing-how-jason-kottke-is-thinking-about-k=
ottke-org-at-20/" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: b=
old;">Jason&#39;s interview in Nieman Lab</a> about writing kottke.org for=
 twenty years=2C and the state and trajectory of the blogosphere.<br>
<br>
<img data-file-id=3D"885551" src=3D"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/f2ef8dc4=
cb32880aecd8d6730/images/6691f125-a2cc-4f99-9434-dcc39ad645f4.png" style=
=3D"border: 0px;margin: 0px;line-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decoratio=
n: none;max-width: 100%;height: auto;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;" wid=
th=3D"NaN"><br>
&nbsp;
<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">My favorite part is where he talks about th=
e site&#39;s anti-mission mission:</p>

<blockquote style=3D"color: #333;padding-left: 25px;padding-right: 25px;ma=
rgin: 0 0 15px;max-width: 100%;">
<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">I think that it&rsquo;s been really hard=2C=
 the last couple of years=2C to cover anything &mdash; I don&rsquo;t know=
 how to say this in a way that isn&rsquo;t going to get all weirdly interp=
reted &mdash; it&rsquo;s been hard to cover anything but things that are s=
erious. Because=2C you know=2C a lot of people &mdash; I think very rightl=
y &mdash; feel that if you&rsquo;re someone who thinks the world is coming=
 down around all of us=2C that you should be on a mission to try to fix th=
at. And I think that there are plenty of sites and plenty of media outlets=
 and plenty of people who are oriented in that direction and moving in tha=
t direction.</p>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">But I don&rsquo;t think kottke.org is one o=
f those things. I think that the site is much more about things that are a=
 little bit more &mdash; I don&rsquo;t want to say <em>hopeful</em>=2C but=
 a lot of it is=2C like=2C <em>look at this cool thing</em>. Look at what=
 humans can do when they have enough time and energy and whatnot to do the=
m! When you called=2C I was had just been watching the SpaceX thing. <a hr=
ef=3D"https://youtu.be/sB_nEtZxPog?t=3D9m15s" style=3D"color: #000000;font=
-weight: bold;">Seeing those two booster rockets land at the same time</a>=
 <em>blew my mind</em>. I was just sitting here=2C yelling=2C like=2C oh m=
y god!</p>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">There has to be room in our culture for tha=
t type of stuff &mdash; that stuff that is inspirational and aspirational=
 &mdash;&nbsp;because it provides some sort of hope that we can actually h=
ave more of that in our lives=2C rather than less.</p>
</blockquote>
I freely admit that this is something Jason does as a blogger way better t=
han I do (along with writing fewer words more often). I think I look at th=
e world and mostly think less &quot;oh my god!&quot; and more &quot;how in=
 the hell does that work?&quot; But I think the two of them have to be com=
plimentary. Learning begins in wonder (the Greeks would call it thauma) as=
 much or more than in criticism (skepsis). And Jason and kottke.org always=
 bring me back to wonder.

<h2 class=3D"null" style=3D"color: #F00A0A;font-size: 22px;line-height: 27=
px;font-weight: bold;margin: 35px 0 10px;">The world and its wonders</h2>
Consider <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/the-wonderful-sounds-of-black=
-ice-skating" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;=
">skating on freshly frozen black lake ice</a>=2C and the wondrous sounds=
 that emits. Think about that for a moment: what could be more mundane=2C=
 more embedded in the history of human experience through most of the worl=
d=2C than frozen water? And yet=2C we&#39;re still able to find ways to ex=
amine it that are new and revealing.<br>
<br>
Photography is quite a bit younger than ice skating=2C and it&#39;s nontri=
vial to get enough light underwater to get great photographs=2C but these=
 <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/winners-of-the-2018-underwater-photog=
rapher-of-the-year-contest" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font=
-weight: bold;">winners of the 2018 underwater photographer contest</a> ma=
nage to show how much wonder is beneath that surface we barely skate upon.=
<br>
<br>
<img data-file-id=3D"885455" src=3D"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/f2ef8dc4=
cb32880aecd8d6730/images/f8a6cb67-4418-4e72-a0b2-3e0f59e0fc00.jpg" style=
=3D"border: 0px;margin: 0px;line-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decoratio=
n: none;max-width: 100%;height: auto;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;" wid=
th=3D"NaN"><br>
<br>
Digging beneath the surface in a different way is this other science photo=
graphy contest winner: a photograph of <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02=
/photo-of-a-single-atom-wins-science-photo-contest" style=3D"color: #00000=
0;font-weight: bold;">a single atom of strontium=2C</a> suspended in an io=
nic trap=2C illuminated by a blue-violet laser. Think about what our machi=
nes can do=2C and all the elements of the universe they can reveal.

<h2 class=3D"null" style=3D"color: #F00A0A;font-size: 22px;line-height: 27=
px;font-weight: bold;margin: 35px 0 10px;">The world and its horrors</h2>
And then you think about what we mostly use our machines to do=2C and thos=
e wonders seem so much rarer and precious. Satellite data shows that <a hr=
ef=3D"https://twitter.com/kottke/status/963531225662042113" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">sea levels will be rising=
 by four inches or more every decade by 2100</a>; this <a href=3D"https://=
kottke.org/18/02/a-map-of-the-world-after-four-degrees-of-warming" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">map of the world w=
ith global temperatures four degrees warmer</a> only shows a few areas los=
t to flooding (never mind that those little dots of red include millions o=
f people)=2C but huge continental belts lost to desertification.<br>
<br>
<img data-file-id=3D"885555" src=3D"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/f2ef8dc4=
cb32880aecd8d6730/images/24543b8b-d203-409c-93bd-670ea0d39f07.jpg" style=
=3D"border: 0px;margin: 0px;line-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decoratio=
n: none;max-width: 100%;height: auto;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;" wid=
th=3D"NaN"><br>
<br>
Meanwhile=2C many of us continue to live in the <a href=3D"https://kottke.=
org/18/02/the-united-states-of-guns-3" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000;font-weight: bold;">United States of Guns</a>=2C where spectacular=
 mass shootings at schools and churches and 33=2C000 gun deaths per annum=
 are just part of the cost of doing <a href=3D"https://twitter.com/kottke/=
status/964153429642874881" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-=
weight: bold;">business</a>. We ride in <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/0=
2/why-speeding-is-so-dangerous" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
font-weight: bold;">high-speed mechanized death machines</a>=2C and that&#=
39;s only changing (if it actually does) because some already rich people=
 will find a way to make money off the transformation.<br>
<br>
At some point=2C we bound ourselves=2C like Odysseus to the mast of his sh=
ip=2C only in reverse. We weren&#39;t afraid the siren&#39;s song would dr=
ive us crazy; we seem to be afraid it might strike us sane and make us giv=
e up the things we&#39;ve come to enjoy.
<h2 class=3D"null" style=3D"color: #F00A0A;font-size: 22px;line-height: 27=
px;font-weight: bold;margin: 35px 0 10px;">So what&#39;s good?</h2>
Black Panther is a great film=2C even if <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/=
02/a-short-melancholy-review-of-black-panther" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">it isn&#39;t exactly the movie I wanted=
 it to be</a>.<br>
<br>
These <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/the-official-painted-portraits-o=
f-barack-and-michelle-obama" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;fon=
t-weight: bold;">portraits of Barack and Michelle Obama</a> are amazing.<b=
r>
<br>
<a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/the-best-audiobooks-for-kids" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">These audiobooks</=
a> are outstanding=2C especially if you have kids.<br>
<br>
<a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/really-excited-for-altos-odyssey-the-s=
equel-to-altos-adventure" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-w=
eight: bold;">Alto&#39;s Odyssey=2C the sequel to Alto&#39;s Adventure=2C<=
/a> looks like it could be fantastic.<br>
<br>
Maybe some day we&#39;ll find our way off that mast=2C and make our way ho=
me.<br>
